<HEADLINE>
BUFFALO, New York: third period.
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Sharks 5, Oilers 3 &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   In Edmonton, Alberta, Marco Sturm had three goals and two
assists as San Jose Sharks extended its winning streak to three
games.
	   The line of Sturm, left wing Jeff Friesen and right wing Alex
Korolyuk combined for 11 points for the Sharks.
	   Sturm scored his seventh and eighth goals in the second period,
and hit an empty net with 1:06 remaining.
	   Friesen had his 10th goal and two assists, and Korolyuk scored
his first goal of the season and also added two assists.
	   Pat Falloon, Todd Marchant and Dean McAmmond scored for the
Oilers as San Jose goalie Mike Vernon gave up more than one goal
for the first time in five games.
</TEXT>
