<SLUG> BC-India-Kashmir Violence,0182 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Seven killed in battle in Indian Kashmiri capital
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SRINAGAR, India (AP) _ An overnight battle that ended with the
army shelling a house in the capital of Indian-held Kashmir left
seven people dead, police said Thursday.
	   The fighting began late Wednesday when police acting on a tip
surrounded a house in a Srinagar neighborhood in a search for
anti-India guerrillas. The people inside opened fire from the
house, killing two police officers. Police returned fire and called
in army reinforcements.
	   The gun battle lasted several hours, ending early Thursday when
the army fired a shell, destroying the three-story house and
damaging several neighboring homes.
	   Five bodies were found inside. Police said two were identified
as guerrillas, while three could not immediately be identified.
	   For the past nine years, nearly a dozen Muslim groups have been
fighting for independence or a merger with neighboring, officially
Islamic Pakistan. Kashmir is the only Muslim-majority state in
predominately Hindu, officially secular India.
</TEXT>
