<SLUG> BC-SKorea-Ford-Kia </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Ford sells stake in Kia Motors
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SEOUL, South Korea (AP) _ Ford Motor Co. said Thursday it has
sold part of its stake in South Korea's Kia Motors Corp.
	   ``A business opportunity presented itself and we took it,'' John
Spelich, a spokesman at Ford's headquarters in Dearborn, Mich.
	   Spelich said Ford sold a 9-percent stake in Kia early this week
but still controls 8 percent in the Korean carmaker through Mazda
Motor Corp. of Japan. Ford is Mazda's largest shareholder.
	   Spelich declined to reveal the buyer and price of the sale.
	   The sale came after Ford had failed to take over Kia in an
international auction in October. South Korea's Hyundai Motor Co.
won the bid to acquire Kia and its commercial vehicle arm, Asia
Motors Co.
	   Officials at Hyundai and Kia declined to comment on the sale.
</TEXT>
