<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-China-Auto Industry </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
China's auto production growth slows
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BEIJING (AP) _ China produced 1.49 million automobiles and sold
1.43 million of them in the first 11 months of 1998, but growth in
both areas slowed from the year before, the state-run Xinhua News
Agency reported Thursday.
	   China's Automotive Industry Development Research Institute said
output growth declined 4 percent and sales growth declined 5
percent compared with the first 11 months of 1997, Xinhua said. The
report gave no actual growth figures for 1998 or 1997.
	   The Chinese auto research organization said state enterprise
restructuring has cut into demand and measures to lift private car
sales have not yet had any real impact.
	   However, a government campaign to boost infrastructure and
construction spending has generated increased demand for heavy-duty
trucks, the report said without providing details.
</TEXT>
