<SLUG> BC-Turkey-Kurdish Bombing,0199 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Kurdish rebel blows up Turkish military bus, two killed, 21
</HEADLINE>
wounded &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   VAN, Turkey (AP) _ A female Kurdish rebel threw herself in front
of a military bus and ignited bombs strapped around her waist,
killing herself, a passerby and wounding 21 officers Thursday,
police said.
	   The attack in downtown Van, a southeastern city bordering Iran
and Iraq, was the third suicide bombing by the Kurdish rebels over
the past three months. The rebels are fighting for autonomy in the
southeast.
	   A police official, speaking on condition of anonymity, said a
15-year-old passerby was killed. None of the injured was in
critical condition, he said.
	   The rebels from the Kurdistan Workers Party, or PKK, have staged
suicide bombings in the past but have increased such attacks since
their leader Abdullah Ocalan was detained in Italy in Nov. 12.
	   Italy later released Ocalan but refused to extradite him to
Turkey, where he could face the death penalty on charges of
terrorism.
	   In the two previous attacks, two female suicide bombers were
killed and a total of 11 people were wounded.
	   The fighting has claimed some 37,000 lives since 1984. 	   
</TEXT>
