<SLUG> BC-Russia-Animal Smugglers </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Russians confiscate smuggled tigers, deer
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Russian customs officials in the Far East seized
the carcasses of endangered tigers and deer during an inspection of
a boat headed to South Korea, a news report said Thursday.
	   Authorities in the port of Vladivostok confiscated the remains
of three tigers, 14 musk deer, the hide of a lynx and a collection
of antlers, the ITAR-Tass news agency reported.
	   In many Asian countries, animal parts are used in traditional
medicines. But the tigers and other animals have been largely wiped
out, and international treaties bar trading in the animal parts,
though smuggling remains a widespread problem.
	   (gm/nw)
