<SLUG> BC-France-Missing Boat </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
French maritime authorities abandon hunt for missing boat
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PARIS (AP) _ French maritime authorities abandoned the search
Thursday for a Spanish fishing boat with eight men aboard that
vanished when a storm hit the southwestern French coast six days
ago.
	   The ``Marero'' is registered in the port of Pasajes in Spain's
Basque province of Guizpoca. The 23-meter (yard) vessel disappeared
Saturday about 90 kilometers (55 miles) north of the French port of
Bayonne during a fierce storm.
	   French authorities searched for the boat for the past two days.
	   France's Center for Monitoring and Sea Rescue coordinated the
search effort. All fishing boats in the area were asked to watch
out for signs of the crew but no trace of them was found.
