<SLUG> BC-Netherlands-Viagra for Women </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Dutch researchers hope to pioneer impotence pill for women
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   AMSTERDAM, Netherlands (AP) _ Three Dutch university hospitals
have joined forces in an effort to pioneer a Viagra-style impotence
pill for women.
	   Pfizer, the U.S. pharmaceutical company that makes Viagra, is
funding the effort by researchers at the principal teaching
hospitals in Amsterdam, the northern city of Groningen and the
southern city of Maastricht, Dutch media reported Thursday.
	   One target of such a pill would be treating the vaginal dryness
that can make intercourse painful, particularly for older women, a
spokesman for the study said.
	   Viagra, while stimulating sexual desire in men, has little or no
effect on increasing a woman's sexual appetite, the researchers
said.
	   (bk)
</TEXT>
