<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Ukraine-Self-Immolation </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Ukrainian bus driver immolates himself over unpaid wages
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KIEV, Ukraine (AP) _ A Ukrainian bus driver doused himself with
gasoline and set himself on fire outside his boss's office,
exasperated that he hadn't received his wages in more than a year,
a newspaper said Thursday.
	   The driver, identified only as Ivan, sustained severe burns to
most of his body before colleagues managed to put out the flames,
the daily Segodnya said.
	   He was hospitalized in critical condition, and was given little
chance of survival, doctors said.
	   The man worked at a municipal transport enterprise in the
southern city of Mykolaiv. He had not been paid for 13 months,
according to Segodnya.
	   Ukraine's economy has contracted sharply since the 1991 Soviet
collapse, and many government and private enterprises do not pay
workers on time.
	   Ukraine's wage debts have been steadily increasing for the past
several years, and now totals about 6.5 billion hryvna (dlrs 1.9
billion), according to government estimates.
	   (vl/nw/gm) 	   
