<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Nepal-Politics,0178 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Koirala sworn in as prime minister
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; AP Photo KAT101 &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   KATMANDU, Nepal (AP) _ Prime Minister Girija Prasad Koirala was
sworn in by King Birendra Thursday to head Nepal's sixth government
in four years, the state-run Radio Nepal said.
	   His Nepali Congress party has the support of the United
Marxist-Leninist Communist Party of Nepal and Nepal Goodwill Party
in parliament. His partner parties are expected to join the
government by the weekend.
	   Koirala resigned on Monday after his coalition partner _ the
Marxist-Leninist Communist Party of Nepal _ withdrew its support
and he lost a majority in Parliament.
	   He came back to power with the help of another communist group.
The new coalition will oversee general elections the government
plans to hold by April.
	   Until 1990, Nepal was an absolute monarchy, but a pro-democracy
movement forced constitutional reforms that reduced King Birendra
to a figurehead. Since then, no party has won a clear majority in
Parliament and successive governments have been short-lived.
</TEXT>
