<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Turkey-Kurdish Bombing, 1st Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Kurdish suicide rebel blows up Turkish military bus, kills
</HEADLINE>
passerby &QL; 
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES with one more injured, CORRECTS that injured also
include civilians &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   VAN, Turkey (AP) _ A Kurdish rebel threw herself in front of a
military bus Thursday and ignited bombs strapped around her waist,
killing herself, a passerby and wounding 22 people, police said.
	   The attack in downtown Van, a southeastern city bordering Iran
and Iraq, was the third such suicide bombing in three months by
rebels fighting for autonomy in the southeast.
	   Gov. Abdulkadir Sari said a passerby, reportedly a 15-year-old
student, was killed. None of the injured, including officers and
civilians employed by the military, was in critical condition, Sari
added.
	   The explosion shattered building windows, including those of a
military residence and the governor's office, the Anatolia news
agency said.
	   The rebels from the Kurdistan Workers Party, or PKK, have
stepped up suicide bombings since their leader Abdullah Ocalan was
detained in Italy on Nov. 12. In two previous attacks, two suicide
bombers were killed and a total of 11 people were wounded.
	   Italy later released Ocalan but refused to extradite him to
Turkey, where he could face the death penalty on charges of
terrorism.
	   The fighting in Turkey has claimed some 37,000 lives since 1984.
	   (sh-fd)
</TEXT>
