<HEADLINE>
Ethnic Albanians claim Serb forces launch lightening attack on
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; URGENT &QL; 
rebel stronghold &QL; 
 &UR; By ISMET HAJDARI &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   PRISTINA, Yugoslavia (AP) _ Serb forces backed by tanks and
artillery launched a strong attack Thursday on a rebel stronghold
north of here, setting fire to houses and killing at least one
person, ethnic Albanian sources said.
	   The Kosovo Information Center, close to the province's ethnic
Albanian leadership, said Serb police and military were targetting
six villages near Podujevo, 32 kilometers (20 miles) north of the
provincial capital Pristina.
	   The report could not be independently confirmed. If the report
is true, the attack would represent a significant setback to the
already shaky cease-fire which ended the worst of the fighting here
in October.
