Dollar mixed, gold falls
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ The U.S. dollar was mixed against other major
currencies in European trading Thursday morning. Gold fell in
London.
	   Dollar rates compared with late Wednesday:
	   _1,6780 German marks, up from 1.6748
	   _116.06 Japanese yen, down from 116.92
	   _1.3695 Swiss francs, up from 1.3660
	   _5.6298 French francs, up from 5.6164
	   _1.8918 Dutch guilders, up from 1.8876
	   _1,662.00 Italian lire, up from 1,659.20
	   _1.5506 Canadian dollars, down from 1.5508
	   The British pound was quoted at dlrs 1.6745, down from dlrs
1.6770.
	   Gold dealers in London fixed a recommended price of dlrs 286.65
bid per troy ounce at midmorning, down from dlrs 287.30 on
Wednesday.
	   Gold fell dlrs 1.90 in Hong Kong to close at dlrs 287.85.
	   Zurich's financial markets were closed for the holiday.
	   Silver opened in London at dlrs 4.90 bid per troy ounce, up from
dlrs 4.89.
	   (acw)
