<SLUG> BC-France-Missing Boat, 1st Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
French maritime authorities abandon hunt for missing boat
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; EDS: UPDATES with Spanish still continuing the search.

<TEXT>
	   PARIS (AP) _ French maritime authorities abandoned the search
Thursday for a Spanish fishing boat with eight men aboard that
vanished when a storm hit the southwestern French coast six days
ago.
	   Spanish authorities, however, were still looking for the
``Marero,'' which is registered in the port of Pasajes in Spain's
Basque province of Guizpoca.
	   Helicopters, a patrol plane, and two tugboats were being used in
the Spanish search Thursday.
	   The 23-meter (yard) vessel disappeared Saturday about 90
kilometers (55 miles) north of the French port of Bayonne during a
fierce storm.
	   French authorities searched for the boat for the past two days.
	   France's Center for Monitoring and Sea Rescue coordinated the
search effort. All fishing boats in the area were asked to watch
out for signs of the crew but no trace of them was found.
	   (parf-dgs) 	   
</TEXT>
