<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Hugary-Drug haul </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Heroin smuggler stopped
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BUDAPEST, Hungary (AP) _ Hungarian customs officers found over
20 kilograms (44 lbs) of heroin in a car driven by a German
citizen, crossing into Austria Thursday, the state news agency MTI
reported,
	   The 36-year-old German citizen was not named, but has been taken
into custody by police at the Hegyeshalom border crossing, 200
kilometers (125 miles) west of Budapest.
	   Forty bags of heroin, with an estimated street value of 120
million forints (dlrs 600,000), were hidden behind the door panels
of the car, according to National Customs spokesman Laszlo Laczo.
	   This was the 151st drug catch this year, Laczo told MTI. So far,
authorities have confiscated a total of 750 kilograms (1,650 lbs)
of illegal drugs, 80 percent of which was heroin. Marijuana,
cocaine, and various amphetamines made up the rest.
	   (ab/me) 	   
</TEXT>
