<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Egypt-Actress </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Rising actress stabs Qatari husband 30 times
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   CAIRO, Egypt (AP) _ A rising Egyptian actress killed her Qatari
husband by stabbing him 30 times, accusing him of being cruel,
jealous and possessive, newspapers reported Thursday.
	   Habiba Mohammed Saeed, 23, confessed to killing her husband
during a quarrel but claimed he tried to kill her first with a
knife, the Al-Gomhuria daily reported.
	   It did not say when the killing occurred or when Saeed was
arrested. She has been charged with premeditated murder, which
carries the death sentence.
	   Saeed told the police that after stabbing Atallah Jaafer
Mohammed, a 33-year-old Qatari businessman, she tied his hands and
legs with a telephone cord. She covered the body with a mattress
and ransacked the flat in a bid to make the police think that he
was killed during a robbery. She then fled.
	   The murder was discovered five days ago when neighbors notified
the police after smelling the odor of Mohammed's decomposing body,
the reports said.
	   Saeed told police that she married Mohammed six months ago and
discovered that he was jealous and wanted her to quit her job.
Saeed began her career as a theater artist, and has acted in some
television serials.
	   On the night of the murder, she said, she demanded an end to
their marriage, but Mohammed refused. In an ensuing quarrel,
Mohammed attacked her with a knife, she said, adding that she
managed to wrest it from his hands and began stabbing him
``unconsciously.''
 &UR; my/vj
</TEXT>
