<SLUG> BC-Kuwait-Military Accident </SLUG>


<TEXT>
	   KUWAIT (AP) _ A U.S. marine was killed and three others injured
when their vehicle rolled over during a military exercise in Kuwait
this week, the U.S. military said Thursday.
	   The marines were in a Humvee, a light desert jeep, when the
accident occurred Monday, the military said in a statement.
	   Lance Cpl. Lucas Williams was killed, said the statement issued
by the 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit. The names of the injured
were not released.
	   The announcement of the accident was delayed until next of kin
had been informed.
