<SLUG> BC-Macedonia-Drugs </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Authorities bust largest marijuana haul at Greek border
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SKOPJE, Macedonia (AP) _ Macedonian customs officials detected
the largest known single haul of marijuana at the country's border
with Greece, media reported Thursday.
	   Over one ton of the narcotic substance, packed in specially
designed small boxes, was discovered late Wednesday in a secret
compartment under the trailer of a truck with Macedonian plates
arriving from Greece.
	   The bust is reportedly the largest single quantity of marijuana
ever confiscated while being smuggled into Macedonia.
	   The street value of one gram of marijuana is priced around dlrs
3 in Macedonia, bringing the estimated total of the haul's worth to
dlrs 1.5 million.
	   The truck driver was immediately arrested but his identity has
not been revealed, Macedonian state radio reported.
	   Macedonian police announced that Prime Minister Ljubco
Georgievski will hold a press conference later Thursday at the
border crossing where the bust was made.
