<HEADLINE>
Two die, one injured, one missing in Ukrainian fire
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KIEV, Ukraine (AP) _ Two workers were killed and one was
hospitalized with severe burns after a fire in a pottery plant in
eastern Ukraine, a news agency reported Thursday. A fourth worker
was missing.
	   The fire at the plant in the village of Budy, in the Kharkiv
region, broke out Wednesday evening and raged for more than four
hours in the plant's packing house, the Interfax news agency said.
	   Another plant worker was still missing after firemen put out the
flames, which damaged a 620 square meter (6,674 square yard) area
and cost the plant around 900,000 hryvna (dlrs 263 million).
	   Plant officials have not yet determined the cause of the fire.
	   (vl/ji) 	   
