<HEADLINE>
Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands from
the National Weather Service.
	   Clouds and showers diminished rapidly over land during the
night. Most of the showers were concentrated over the Caribbean
waters about 20 to 50 miles south of St. Croix and Puerto Rico.
	   Nevertheless, the winds remained very strong over land with San
Juan reporting gusts to more than 25 mph. Doppler radar also
detected winds up to 35 mph over the highlands of Puerto Rico.
	   These windy conditions will continue across Puerto Rico and the
U.S. Virgin Islands today as a surface high over the northeast
Atlantic continues to be the dominant weather system over our area.
	   A wind advisory continues in effect at least through noon. These
winds will also bring scattered to numerous showers, especially
over the U.S. Virgin Islands and the northeast sections of Puerto
Rico.
	   However, most of the showers will be light to moderate, so the
rainfall accumulations will generally be less than a quarter of an
inch.
	   Northeast winds at 20 to 25 kts will be affecting all our
coastal waters today with occasional gusts to 30 kts, mainly over
the Atlantic waters.
	   These winds will continue to produce rough seas up to 11 feet in
northeast swells. Consequently, a small craft advisory remains in
effect for all our coastal waters.
	   San Juan and the northern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Wind advisory in effect for elevations above 1,000 feet.
	   Today... Variable cloudiness and continued breezes. Good chance
of showers. High 80 to 85. Wind northeast 15 to 25 mph, except 25
to 30 mph in higher elevations. Chance of rain is 50 percent.
	   Tonight... Variable cloudiness and continued breezes with a 60
percent chance of showers. Low 70 to 75. Wind northeast 15 to 25
mph.
	   Christmas day... Variable cloudiness and breezy with a 50
percent chance of showers. High 80 to 85. Wind northeast to east 15
to 20 mph with higher gusts.
	   Remainder of Christmas weekend... Variable cloudiness with
scattered to numerous showers. Chance for thunderstorms. Highs 80
to 85. Low 70 to 75.
	   Eastern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Wind advisory in effect for elevations above 1,000 feet.
	   Today... Variable cloudiness and continued breezy with a 50
percent chance of showers. High 80 to 85. Wind northeast 15 to 25
mph, except 25 to 30 mph in higher elevations.
	   Tonight... Variable cloudiness and continued breezes with a 60
percent chance of showers. Low 70 to 75. Wind northeast 15 to 25
mph with higher gusts.
	   Christmas day... Variable cloudiness and breezy with a 50
percent chance of showers. High 80 to 85. Wind northeast 15 to 20
mph with higher gusts.
	   Remainder of Christmas weekend... Variable cloudiness with
scattered to numerous showers. Chance for thunderstorms. Highs 80
to 85. Low 70 to 75.
	   Ponce and the southern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Wind advisory in effect for elevations above 1,000 feet...
	   Today... Variable cloudiness and breezy with a 30 percent chance
of showers. High 85 to near 90. Wind east 15 to 25 mph... Except 25
to 30 mph higher elevations.
	   Tonight... Variable cloudiness and continued breezy with a 30
percent chance of showers. Low 70 to 75. Wind northeast 5 to 10
mph... Except 15 to 20 mph higher elevations.
	   Christmas day... Variable cloudiness with scattered showers.
High 85 to 90. Chance of rain 40 percent. Wind northeast 15 to 20
mph... Except southeast along the coast.
	   Remainder of Christmas weekend... Variable cloudiness with
scattered to numerous showers. Chance for thunderstorms. Highs 80
to 85. Low 70 to 75.
	   Mayaguez and the western sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Wind advisory in effect for elevations above 1,000 feet.
	   Today... Variable cloudiness and windy with a 30 percent chance
of showers, mainly in the afternoon. High 80 to near 90. Wind
northeast 20 to 30 mph.
	   Tonight... Variable cloudiness and continued breezy with a 30
percent chance of showers. Low 70 to 75. Wind northeast 15 to 25
mph with higher gusts.
	   Christmas day... Variable cloudiness and breezy with a 40
percent chance of showers. High 80 to 85. Wind northeast 15 to 20
mph with higher gusts.
	   Remainder of Christmas weekend... Variable cloudiness with
scattered to numerous showers. Chance for thunderstorms. Highs 80
to 85. Low 70 to 75.
	   Interior sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Wind advisory in effect for elevations above 1,000 feet.
	   Today... Variable cloudiness and windy with a 40 percent chance
of showers. High of 70 in the mountains, 80 in lower elevations.
Wind northeast 20 to 30 mph with higher gusts.
	   Tonight... Variable cloudiness and continued wind with a 50
percent chance of showers. Low 60 to 65 in the mountains; 65 to 70
in lower valleys. Wind northeast 20 to 25 mph with higher gusts.
	   Christmas day... Variable cloudiness and breezy. A 50 percent
chance of showers. High 70 mountains to 80 low elevations. Wind
northeast 15 to 20 with higher gusts.
	   Remainder of Christmas weekend... Variably cloudy with scattered
to numerous showers. Chance for thunderstorms. Highs 70 to 80. Low
60 to 70.
	   St. Thomas, St. John and the Adjacent Islands-St. Croix:
	   Wind advisory in effect.
	   Today... Variable cloudiness and continued breezy. A good chance
of showers. High around 85. Wind northeast 15 to 25 mph with higher
gusts. Chance of rain is 50 percent.
	   Tonight... Variable cloudiness and continued breezy with a 60
percent chance of showers. Low 70 to 75. Wind northeast 15 to 25
mph with higher gusts.
	   Christmas day... Variable cloudiness and breezy with a 50
percent chance of showers. High near 85. Winds northeast 15 to 20
mph with higher gusts.
	   Remainder of Christmas weekend... Variably cloudy with scattered
to numerous showers. Chance for thunderstorms. Highs 80 to 85. Low
70 to 75.
	   Atlantic waters north and northeast of Puerto Rico and the U.S.
Virgin Islands:
	   Small craft advisory in effect.
	   This afternoon... Wind mainly northeast 20 to 25 kt and gusty.
Seas 9 to 11 ft in northeast swells. Widely scattered showers.
	   Tonight... Wind northeast 20 to 25 kt. Seas 9 to 11 ft in
northeast swells. Scattered showers, more numerous in eastern
waters.
	   Friday... Wind northeast to east 20 to 25 kt. Seas 9 to 11 ft in
northeast swells. Scattered showers.
	   Caribbean waters south and southeast of Puerto Rico and the U.S.
Virgin Islands:
	   Small craft advisory in effect.
	   This afternoon... Wind mainly northeast 20 to 25 kt and gusty.
Near shore seas 6 to 8 ft and off shore seas 8 to 10 ft. in east to
northeast swells. Scattered showers.
	   Tonight... Wind northeast 20 to 25 kt. Near shore seas 6 to 8 ft
and off shore seas 8 to 10 ft. in east to northeast swells.
Scattered showers, more numerous in eastern waters.
	   Friday... Wind northeast to east around 20 kt. Near shore seas 5
to 7 ft and offshore seas 7 to 9 ft. in east to northeast swells.
Scattered showers.
	   Near shore waters of western Puerto Rico:
	   Small craft advisory in effect.
	   This afternoon... Wind mainly northeast 15 to 25 kt and gusty.
Seas 3 to 5 ft. Widely scattered showers.
	   Tonight... Wind northeast 10 to 20 kt. Seas 3 to 4 ft. Widely
scattered showers.
	   Friday... Wind northeast to e 10 to 20 kt. Seas 3 to 4 ft.
Widely scattered showers.
	   Outlook for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands waters:
	   Friday night through Monday... Surface trough will move from the
Lesser Antilles west across the local area Friday night to
Saturday, producing a decrease in winds and seas.
	   Wind east to southeast 15 to 20 kt Saturday, increasing to 20 to
25 kt from the east on Sunday.
	   Seas 6 to 8 ft in trade wind swells in both Atlantic and
Caribbean waters through Saturday night, possibly building to 8 to
10 ft again Sunday through Monday.
