<HEADLINE>
Rangers finally sign German goalkeeper
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   GLASGOW, Scotland (AP) _ Glasgow Rangers ended the long-running
saga of finding a replacement 'keeper for injured Frenchman Lionel
Charbonnier on Thursday by hiring Stafan Klos from Borussia
Dortmund.
	   The 27-year-old German international accepted a four-year
contract worth 700,000 pounds (dlrs 1.2 million) and could make his
Scottish premier league debut against St. Johnstone at Ibrox on
Saturday.
	   Klos was expected to sign with Rangers in the summer but a legal
dispute with Bundesliga club Dortmund forced him to see out his
contract in the German league.
