<HEADLINE>
Blackburn close to agreement with Ward
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BLACKBURN, England (AP) _ Struggling Premier League team
Blackburn Rovers is expected to bolster its playing staff in the
New Year after agreeing terms with Barnsley for striker Ashley
Ward.
	   The 28-year-old forward is negotiating personal terms with
Rovers and appears set to accept a deal worth 4.25 million pounds
(dlrs 7.1 million).
	   Ward will be Brian Kidd's second major acquisition since taking
the helm at Ewood Park.
	   Kidd started his bid to avoid relegation by signing Northern
Ireland winger Keith Gillespie from Newcastle in a 2.35
million-pound (dlrs 3.9 million) deal earlier this month.
	   Blackburn spokesman Tom Finn confirmed Thursday that Rovers had
agreed terms with division one team Barnsley but said negotiations
with Ward had just started and were expected to continue after
Christmas.
	   ``(Ward) was suspended from the Boxing Day action and we were
unable to get things sorted to make him eligible for Monday
(against Leicester),'' he said.
	   (jp)
</TEXT>
