<HEADLINE>
Report: U.S. tourist tried to smuggle dlrs 125,000 in cash from
</HEADLINE>
Russia &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ An American tourist was stopped at Moscow's
international airport Thursday for allegedly trying to smuggle dlrs
125,000 in cash out of Russia, a news report said.
	   Russian customs officials said the money was hidden in the man's
luggage, the Interfax news agency reported. They said he was a
tourist returning from Moscow to New York. No other details were
immediately available.
	   Also on Thursday, customs officials confiscated dlrs 40,000 in
undeclared cash from the luggage of a Czech Republic national, who
was flying to Prague, Interfax reported.
	   Customs officials at Sheremetyevo airport also confiscated five
bars of gold, weighing about 1 kilogram (2.2 pounds), from a
Vietnamese citizen, the report said.
	   A criminal investigation has been launched in each case.
	   Russia's State Customs Committee said Thursday that in the first
six months of the year, officers confiscated around dlrs 5 million
and 430 kilograms (946 pounds) of gold from suspected smugglers,
Interfax reported.
