<HEADLINE>
Trio caught tunneling to bank vault; one escapes among Xmas
</HEADLINE>
shoppers

<TEXT>
	   CAEN, France (AP) _ One of three men caught tunneling to a bank
vault managed to escape police by fleeing into crowds of Christmas
Eve shoppers in this Normandy town Thursday.
	   The trio in their mid-20s was digging a tunnel to the vault of a
Societe Generale in downtown Caen overnight Tuesday when police
caught them in the act, managing to arrest two of them. The other
fled into the night.
	   On Thursday morning, police had driven the two handcuffed
suspects from jail to the courthouse downtown when one of them
broke away from two escorting officers and ran, officials said on
customary anonymity.
	   With his hands cuffed behind his back, the suspect managed to
evade officers after a short pursuit, blending into crowds of
Christmas shoppers in the commercial district, authorities said.
	   Officials declined to identify the suspects but said the two
were locals with past police records.
