	   WASHINGTON _ Presidential scholars predict that after enduring
impeachment, President Bill Clinton can't expect to accomplish much
in his final two years in office. US-CLINTON. Expected by 2100 GMT.
By Connie Cass.
	   MOSCOW _ Parliament gives quick initial approval to the draft
1999 budget Thursday, stoking hopes that the hard-liners who
dominate the legislature would cooperate with the government to
pull Russia out of its economic crisis. RUSSIA-ECONOMY. Lead has
moved. By Anna Dolgov. AP Photos MOSB104,114.
	   ISLAMABAD, Pakistan _ In his first public denial of involvement
in the U.S. Embassy bombings in Africa, Osama bin Laden says he is
innocent but not sorry the attacks happened, a Pakistani news
agency reports Thursday. AFGHANISTAN-BIN LADEN. Has moved. By Kathy
Gannon.
	   BONN, Germany _ Facing their first big crisis, Chancellor
Gerhard Schroeder and his Greens party allies insist Thursday that
a feud over scrapping nuclear power won't break up the 2-month-old
German government. GERMANY-POLITICS. Has moved. By Tony Czuczka.
	   JERUSALEM _ Retired Gen. Amnon Lipkin-Shahak barely opens his
mouth to declare his entry into the political arena Thursday before
he is plastered with labels _ newcomer, old hat, cynic, naif. He
can expect more of the same in the rough and tumble of Israeli
politics. ISRAEL-POLITICS. Expected by 2100 GMT. By Ron Kampeas. AP
Photos TLV101, JRL103.
	   TEHRAN, Iran _ An appeals court reduces the jail sentence of a
former Tehran mayor convicted of corruption from five years to two
years, a judiciary statement says Thursday. IRAN-MAYOR. Has moved.
