u i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Yugoslavia-Kosovo UPDATE   12-24 0225
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Yugoslavia-Kosovo, UPDATE </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Albania calls for international pressure on Serbia
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TIRANA, Albania (AP) _ The Albanian government urged NATO on
Thursday to intervene to stop fighting in Kosovo in wake of a Serb
offensive against ethnic Albanian rebels in the Podujevo area.
	   ``The Albanian government calls the international community to
use all measures to avoid a new wave of genocide in Kosovo after
the last Serbian offensive in Podujevo region,'' the Albanian
foreign ministry said in a statement.
	   It said that renewing the conflict in Kosovo would be
``extremely dangerous for the peace and the stability in all the
region. The political pressure on Belgrade should be continued with
all necessary measures.''
	   The Albanians said NATO intervention ``is necessary to end the
Kosovo drama and also to give to this question the desired solution
from all the parties.''
	   Speaking to parliament, Albanian Prime Minister Pandeli Majko
accused the Yugoslav government of trying to provoke a renewal of
fighting.
	   ``The stand of the Albanian government is clear,'' he said. ``We
respect the will of the Albanians of Kosovo and also we respect the
international principals. We call the political forces of Kosovo to
unify their stands and also we call the political parties of
Albania to agree on one stand on Kosovo issue.''
</TEXT>
