<SLUG> BC-France-Yugoslavia </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
France condemns Serb attacks in Kosovo
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PARIS (AP) _ France on Thursday condemned ``with the greatest
firmness'' the resumption of Serb attacks in the restive Yugoslav
province of Kosovo, calling them disproportionate to recent Kosovo
rebel activity.
	   At the same time, France criticized ``provocation by the UCK''
rebels as ``unjustifiable ... feeding the cycle of attacks and
repression,'' Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Anne Gazeau-Secret said
in a statement.
	   She referred to a recent attack in which six Serbs were killed
in the town of Pec.
	   Aware of ``the risks of a resumption of hostilities and the
escalation of violence,'' France called for ``a commitment toward a
political dialogue between the two parties,'' the spokeswoman said.
	   (cb-parf)
</TEXT>
