<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Russia-Politics </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Chernomyrdin's party removes parliamentary leader
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Members of former Prime Minister Viktor
Chernomyrdin's political movement party followed his lead on
Thursday and voted to replace their parliamentary leader.
	   Thirty-six members of the Our Home is Russia parliamentary
grouping voted for removing Alexander Shokhin from the leadership
post, while four supported him, Russian media reported.
	   Shokhin said he would leave the parliamentary grouping.
	   ``I will build an independent political career,'' Shokhin was
quoted as saying by the Interfax news agency.
	   Chernomyrdin accused Shokhin of weakening the parliamentary
grouping and not consulting enough with other leaders of the
movement.
	   For his part, Shokhin has departed from the party line on
several issues. He recently publicly supported forming an alliance
with Moscow Mayor Yuri Luzhkov, and two days ago he proposed
replacing the leadership of Our Home Is Russia, including
Chernomyrdin himself.
	   Shokhin served 10 days as deputy prime minister in charge of
financial policy under Prime Minister Yevgeny Primakov before
resigning and returning to his parliamentary post. At the time of
his resignation, he expressed frustration about the differences
among Cabinet members over Russia's economic strategy.
	   He had served as deputy premier and economics minister at the
start of Russia's free-market reforms in 1992-95.
	   (ji) 	   
</TEXT>
