<SLUG> BC-Balloon Quest-Glance,0184 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Facts about route being taken by round-the-world balloonists
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; With Balloon Quest &QL; 
 &UR; By The Associated Press &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   Facts about the route being taken by three balloonists trying
for the first nonstop balloon flight around the world:
	   _The balloon lifted off from Marrakech, Morocco, on Dec. 18, and
flew over Algeria, Libya and Turkey.
	   _ The balloon missed Iraq by 60 miles (97 kilometers), Iran by
seven miles (12 kilometers) and Russia by 10 miles (16 kilometers)
_ three countries that had denied them permission to cross.
	   _The three flew over Central Asia to the Himalayas and into
China, where they were permitted to travel below 26 degrees north
latitude.
	   _They drifted into prohibited territory and after two days left
China, crossed Japan, and set out across the Pacific Ocean.
	   _They passed the halfway mark around 1400 GMT Thursday.
	   _The balloonists planned to reach North America sometime
Christmas Day over Washington state or southern Canada.
	   _They hope to touch down in western Europe to end the
24,000-mile (38,600-kilometer) flight. 	   
</TEXT>
