w2614 &Cx1f; wstm-
u i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Turkey-ChristmasMass     12-24 0179
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Turkey-Christmas Mass </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
With BC-Italy-Kurdish Leader
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Citing security fears, Catholic church in Istanbul calls off
Midnight Mass &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   ISTANBUL, Turkey (AP) _ Istanbul's largest Roman Catholic Church
called off Christmas Eve midnight Mass, citing security concerns
due to strong anti-Italian sentiment over Italy's harboring of a
Kurdish rebel.
	   ``There will be no midnight service this year,'' said a notice
at the entrance of St. Anthony's church.
	   Church officials told Turkey's Anatolia news agency a service
would be held Friday morning.
	   Italy's refusal to extradite Kurdish rebel leader Abdullah
Ocalan to Turkey for trial has angered many Turks, sparking violent
anti-Italian protests and boycotts on Italian goods.
	   Istanbul is an overwhelmingly Islamic country with only a tiny
Christian minority. In 1996, a concussion bomb placed in a
confessional in St. Anthony's went off during a service at the
church. No one was injured.
	   The war between Kurdish rebels and Turkey's military has killed
37,000 since 1984.
	   (sh) 	   
</TEXT>
