<SLUG> BC-Sports-Basketball-NBA Lockout, 4th Ld,0170 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Two sides in US basketball dispute meet in Los Angeles
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: ADDS sources telling AP deal is still possible &QL; 
 &UR; By RONALD BLUM &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   NEW YORK (AP) _ U.S. National Basketball Association
commissioner David Stern and union director Billy Hunter held a
secret meeting in Los Angeles Wednesday night, a few hours after
the league said a settlement must be reached by Jan. 7 to save the
season.
	   An NBA spokesman confirmed the meeting, which was the first
between the men since Dec. 11.
	   It took place at the office of agent Leonard Armato, who in the
past has tried to act as a peacemaker between Stern and Hunter.
	   ``Absolutely no progress was made,'' NBA spokesman Brian
McIntyre said. ``There may or may not be another meeting over the
weekend.'' Yet sources on both sides of the talks told The
Associated Press that a deal could be done quickly if they could
agree to swap major concessions.
	    &UR; Armato, who ... 5th graf pvs
