<HEADER>
w2631 &Cx1f; wstm-
r i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Barbados-Marijuana     12-24 0145
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Barbados-Marijuana,0147 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Woman carries a baby on one arm, 81 pounds of marijuana on the
</HEADLINE>
other &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   BRIDGETOWN, Barbados (AP) _ When 23-year-old Andonia Lynch
walked off the airplane in Barbados, customs officials were
impressed to see her managing a baby on one arm and an 81-pound
(36-kilogram) suitcase on the other.
	   They were even more impressed, however, by the luggage's
contents _ bags and bags of high-quality marijuana that had escaped
a recent police sweep of marijuana farms and processing huts on the
nearby island of St. Vincent.
	   Lynch, a St. Vincent native, was convicted Thursday of drug
trafficking and sentenced to three years in jail.
	   She was detained Monday night at the Bridgetown airport.
	   Magistrate Valton Bend ordered the 11-month-old baby into
government custody until family members in St. Vincent claim it.
</TEXT>
