	    &UR; MAIN SPOT NEWS:
	   BETHLEHEM, West Bank _ Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat attends
Christmas Eve celebrations in Bethlehem, while Pope John Paul II
looks forward to the jubilee year that will begin Christianity's
third millenium. CHRISTMAS ROUNDUP. Recap expected by 0200 GMT. By
Mark Lavie. AP Photos JRL106-111,113-116.
	   ALSO MOVED:
	   _POPE-CHRISTMAS. Pope John Paul II looks forward to the year
2000. Developing, recap expected by 0200 GMT. AP Photos covering.
	   _POPE-CHRISTMAS-TEXT.
	   _NICARAGUA-CHRISTMAS-MITCH. Grim Christmas for survivors of
Hurricane Mitch.
	   _CUBA-CHRISTMAS. Cuba celebrates newly legalized Christmas
holiday. AP Photos HAV101-103.
	   _CHRISTMAS IN IRAQ. Christmas in Iraq amid deprivation, sorrow.
	   _TURKEY-CHRISTMAS MASS. Citing security fears, Catholic church
in Istanbul calls off Midnight Mass.
	   _NEW ZEALAND-ANTARCTIC-CHRISTMAS. Ice trekkers spend Christmas
at place never before visited by man. Has moved to some points;
expected to others by 0200 GMT.
	   PODUJEVO, Yugoslavia _ Brushing aside NATO and U.S. warnings,
Serb tanks and troops strike a Kosovo Albanian rebel stronghold.
YUGOSLAVIA-KOSOVO. Recap expected by 0300 GMT. By Misha Savic. AP
PHotos BEL101-103.
	   BAGHDAD, Iraq _ Air raid sirens sound in Baghdad early Friday,
but motorists seem to ignore them. The United States denies
carrying out any military action to cause the warning. IRAQ. Recap
expected by 0200 GMT. AP Photos BAG104-106.
	   JERUSALEM _ The only thing Israel's former chief of staff did
was give back his uniform, declare an interest in political life,
and mouth a few pieties about hope and getting along. In an
election year, that's enough to spark a war. ISRAEL-POLITICS. Lead
has moved. By Ron Kampeas. AP Photos TLV101-103, JRL103.
	   MOSCOW _ Parliament gives quick initial approval to the draft
1999 budget, raising hopes that the hard-liners who dominate the
legislature would cooperate with the government to pull Russia out
of its economic crisis. RUSSIA-ECONOMY. Lead has moved. By Anna
Dolgov. AP Photos MOSB104,114.
	   ISLAMABAD, Pakistan _ In his first public denial of involvement
in the U.S. Embassy bombings in Africa, Osama bin Laden says he is
innocent but not sorry the attacks happened, a Pakistani news
agency reports. AFGHANISTAN-BIN LADEN. Recap expected by 0300 GMT.
By Kathy Gannon.
	   WASHINGTON _ Presidential scholars predict that after enduring
impeachment, President Bill Clinton can't expect to accomplish much
in his final two years in office. US-CLINTON. Has moved. By Connie
Cass.
	   LONDON _ Three balloonists streak across the Pacific Ocean on a
jetstream, hoping to elude a troublesome weather pattern that could
threaten their bid to achieve the first non-stop trip around the
world in a balloon. BALLOON QUEST. Recap expected by 0300 GMT. AP
