	   WORLD SPORTS AT 0000 GMT
 &UR; SOCCER:
	   BLACKBURN, England _ Struggling Premier League team Blackburn
Rovers expects to bolster its playing staff in 1999 after agreeing
terms with Barnsley for striker Ashley Ward.
	   Slug Sports-Soccer-Blackburn-Ward. Has moved.
	   WEST BROMWICH, England _ An English soccer fan became so
frustrated with the performance of his home team that he reported
them to the authorities. The Trading Standards Authority, that is.
He says he's not getting his money's worth.
	   Slug Sports-Soccer-England-Backlash Continues. Has moved.
 &UR; CRICKET:
	   WELLINGTON, New Zealand _ After an abandoned first test due to
rain, New Zealand and India make final preparations for Saturday's
second test at the Basin Reserve.
	   BC-Sports-Cricket-New Zealand-India. Expected by 0800GMT.
	   By Ihithisham Kamardeen.
	   MELBOURNE, Australia _ England faces a morning workout and the
Ashes-holding Australians a Christmas lunch as both teams prepare
for Saturday's fourth test.
	   BC-Sports-Cricket-Australia-England. Expected by 0900GMT.
 &UR; OLYMPICS:
	   NEW YORK _ As the International Olympic Committee wrestles with
the greatest ethics scandal and three panels probe alleged bribery
in Salt Lake City's quest for the Winter Games, IOC members and
bidding cities face the issue of where friendliness ends and
corruption begins.
