<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-UN-People-Annan,0138 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Not even 5, boy calls on Annan to work for world peace
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   UNITED NATIONS (AP) _ Lucas Olson Duffy hasn't even reached his
fifth birthday yet, but he already has the makings of a diplomat
and some definite ideas about world peace.
	   In a letter to U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan, he said:
``Please talk to the president of Iraq. Please make up. Work it
out.''
	   The letter, hand printed with slightly crooked letters, is
signed ``Lucas,'' who is ``age 4 11/12.''
	   The secretary-general sent a thank you letter to Lucas, a
student at the U.N. International School.
	   ``I am glad to see that one is never too young to speak out for
peace,'' he said. ``I promise you I will work very hard for peace,
in Iraq and everywhere else in the world.''
</TEXT>
